data.title: England Premier League 2009/10, Results and Standings
data.meta_description: Statistics, results and standings from the England Premier League 2009/10
data.text:
Did you know...

Two players share the glory of being top goalscorers at the Olympic Football Tournament - Sophus Nielsen (Denmark) and Antal Dunai (Hungary) each scored 13 times. A close second is Dunai's compatriot, Ferenc Bene, who netted all twelve of his goals in one single Tournament - in 1964, contributing largely to Hungary's ultimate gold medal.
